    slug: "imam-sufiyan-bin-uyaniyah-may-allah-have-mercy-upon-him",
    description: `Imam Sufiyan Bin Uyaniyah (May Allah have mercy upon him) is an Urdu-language biographical book that presents the life and scholarly contributions of Imam Sufyan ibn Uyaynah (107-198 AH / 725-814 CE), one of the most prominent hadith scholars and Quran exegetes of the second century of Islam, whose authority in hadith narration was so widely recognized that Imam Ahmad ibn Hanbal famously said about him, "If Sufyan ibn Uyaynah had not been alive, the knowledge of the Hijaz would have vanished." The book provides a detailed account of this towering figure of early Islamic scholarship, tracing his life from his birth in Kufah to his long career as a teacher and muhaddith in Makkah, where he became one of the most sought-after hadith authorities in the entire Muslim world.

The book covers the educational background of Imam Sufyan ibn Uyaynah, who was born into a family of scholars and began his pursuit of Islamic knowledge at a young age. He studied under many of the leading Tabi'in (the generation of Muslims who succeeded the companions of the Prophet) and their students, giving him a remarkably short chain of narration to the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) that enhanced the value of his hadith transmissions. The book details his relocation to Makkah, where he lived for most of his adult life and where he taught hadith and tafsir (Quranic exegesis) for decades, attracting students from every corner of the Muslim world. His students included some of the most important scholars of the next generation, such as Imam al-Shafi'i, who was among his most devoted pupils and who held him in the highest esteem.

The book examines Imam Sufyan's dual expertise in both hadith and tafsir, noting that he was equally renowned for his mastery of Quranic interpretation and his knowledge of hadith. His tafsir was characterized by a focus on the interpretation of the Quran through other Quranic verses, authentic hadith, and the statements of the companions, following the methodology of the early generations of Muslim scholars. The book discusses his famous views on various topics, including his position on matters of theology, his approach to hadith criticism, and his method of resolving apparent contradictions between different narrations. The book also covers his personal character, describing his piety, his generosity, his humility despite his immense scholarly stature, and his approach to life and worship. The Urdu prose is narrative and well-sourced, with references to the major biographical dictionaries and hadith works that document Imam Sufyan's life and contributions. This book is a valuable resource for students of Islamic history, hadith scholars, and anyone interested in the lives of the early generations of Islamic scholars whose work forms the foundation of the Muslim intellectual tradition.`,
    metaDescription: "Imam Sufiyan Bin Uyaniyah is an Urdu biography of the great hadith scholar and exegete. Covers his life, teachers, students including Imam Shafi'i, and scholarship."
